{"source_key":"sha256-5554f84e350d12a12ce22886a954582c","record_index":488,"record_hash":"sha256:0a004ce456a0db943a20fb343b7a914b0c720c0aff865be729cd1435781c38e8","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:41:29.217Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"It would take a small real feature, not a polish tweak.\n\nThe race is here: `write_transcript_batch()` reads `:turns` and `:record-hashes`, decides which records are new, builds a turn, then calls `apply_edits()`. The write batch is atomic, but the read plus decision is not.\n\nSo two captures can do this:\n\n1. both read the same old `record-hashes`\n2. both accept the same “new” records\n3. both create turns\n4. both append transcript/turn entries\n\nFor identical records, the hash set eventually dedupes, but the transcript list and turns list can get duplicate entries. For different records, both turns can point to the same `previous_turn_key`, so the turn chain forks.\n\nI’d fix it with a local capture lock first. Cheapest sane version:\n\n- Add a repo-local advisory lock, probably under GitButler storage or `.git`, scoped to agentlog capture.\n- Acquire it around:\n  - read `:turns`\n  - read `:record-hashes`\n  - dedupe/accept records\n  - capture environment\n  - build turn summary/detail\n  - `apply_edits`\n- Release after `apply_edits`.\n- Add a concurrency test with two threads/processes trying to capture the same growing transcript.\n\nThat’s maybe half a day including tests, assuming the lock primitive is straightforward.\n\nThe cleaner but bigger fix is a GitMeta compare-and-write API: “apply these edits only if key X still has version/hash Y.” Then we can avoid holding a lock during environment capture by retrying if the session changed. But that means changing GitMeta/lib semantics, adding version reads or conditional edits, then adapting capture. Better architecture, more blast radius.\n\nMy pick: do the local lock now. It’s boring, effective, and keeps the fix inside `but-agentlog`. The optimistic GitMeta API can wait until more callers need it.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:41:29.217Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}